3) Conclusion — why I choose CD 2 and reject CD 1:
- I choose CD 2 because it aligns with the core of my listening values: close‑miked, people‑in‑a‑room immediacy; forward, breathy lead vocals and generous vocal takes; piano and subtle acoustic textures that keep arrangements spare and song‑serving; mid‑focused tape warmth with transparent, low‑compression mastering that preserves microdynamics and avoids loudness chasing. Those features directly satisfy my preference for intimate vocal interplay and restrained, vintage‑immediacy production.
